On Friday, November 10, 2006 7:19 AM Franz wrote:
>=20
> I=B4m a WinTeXmacs user since a few days, and I=B4m using (and=20
> needing) it only as a frontend for Axiom (latest versions:=20
> Axiom 0.1.4 and WinTeXmacs 1.0.5).
>=20
> First I had big problems to start an Axiom session at all (I=20
> always got the error message "Could not create pipe" in=20
> WinTeXmacs), until I found the reason for this problem after=20
> quite a lot of trials:
> The line =B4(:launch "tm_axiom")=B4 of the file =B4init-axiom.scm=B4=20
> in the folder
> =B4...\WinTeXmacs\TeXmacs\plugins\axiom\progs\init-axiom.scm=B4=20
> doesn=B4t work!
> When I insert a space after =B4tm_axiom=B4, then it works - so=20
> this line shoud be:
> (:launch "tm_axiom ")
>=20
> Ok, at least Axiom is now =B4running=B4 under WinTeXmacs as a=20
> session, but it is not =B4working=B4, at least not correctly!
> There are 2 main problems I=B4ve found yet:
>=20
> 1) Since Axiom uses a space (=B4 =B4) instead of a multiplication=20
> character (=B4*=B4) in the output, such expressions are displayed=20
> terribly in WinTexmacs.
> Trying e.g. "factor(15)" displays "35" in WinTeXmacs, where=20
> of course there actually IS a space between 3 and 5, but you=20
> can=B4t see it (since this space is too small)!
> This problem is even more dramatically for variables:
> Entering e.g. "x*y-xy" gives the result "xy-xy" ...
>=20
> 2) Even correctly formatted results from Axiom are displayed=20
> wrong in WinTeXmacs - here=B4s only one example:
> Entering "xy/y" gives the following output:
>  y
> x-
>  y
>=20
> (If that=B4s not correctly displayed here, it=B4s a "x"=20
> immediately followed by a fraction "y/y")
> Here WinTeXmacs seem to interpret "xy" as if it would be "x=20
> y", although Axiom is correctly returning a TeX expression=20
> =B4xy \over y=B4!
>=20
> So only these 2 problems are absolutely enough, to not trust=20
> any WinTeXmacs output of Axiom results at all - maybe you can=20
> imagine, what terribly wrong =B4results=B4 would happen for more=20
> complicated expressions ...
>=20
> Is there any way to solve these problems?
> Or is there a newer version of the Axiom-WinTeXmacs interface=20
> (tm_axiom) available, where these bugs have been fixed?
>=20
> Well, I hope so - otherwise we can simply forget using Axiom=20
> as a WinTeXmacs session ... :-(
>=20

I presume that you are aware of the following page on the Axiom
Wiki?

http://wiki.axiom-developer.org/TeXmacs

If you installed Axiom-0.1.4 after WinTeXmacs (and therefore the
Axiom programs appear before any other in the PATH) then you should
be using a modified version of tm_axiom distributed with Axiom (see
info on above web page). In that case, setting the following options
at the top of your TeXmacs document might help:

  )set output texmacs over no
  )set output texmacs space yes

You can also set these are default by creating an environment
variable

  TM_AXIOM=3D'over no, space yes'

If you have problems with the Axiom verison of tm_axiom then you
can also report them here:

http://wiki.axiom-developer.org/IssueTracker

or on the Axiomm Developer list

  axiom-developer@nongnu.org

BTW: Welcome to Axiom. :-) We are actively looking for people to do
Axiom development on Windows. Please drop in if you are interested.

Regards,
Bill Page.



